  "prob_desc_input_spec": "The first line contains three integers n, a and b (1 ≤ a, b ≤ 100, 2 ≤ n ≤ a + b) — the number of plates, the number of pieces of the first cake, and the number of pieces of the second cake, respectively.",
  "prob_desc_notes": "NoteIn the first example there is only one way to distribute cakes to plates, all of them will have 1 cake on it.In the second example you can have two plates with 3 and 4 pieces of the first cake and two plates both with 5 pieces of the second cake. Minimal number of pieces is 3.",
